<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68b293a-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10310"><num value="10310">§ 10310.</num><heading> Discharge</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A master shall deliver to a seaman a full and true account of the seaman’s wages and all deductions at least 48 hours before paying off or discharging the seaman.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68b293b-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/564">97 Stat. 564</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/206/tIV/s408">Pub. L. 103–206, title IV, § 408</ref>, <date date="1993-12-20">Dec. 20, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2436">107 Stat. 2436</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
